ANTHRAX - KYRGYZSTAN: (OSH) BOVINE, OIE
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 17 Mar 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2016; 29(11) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19939


Anthrax, Kyrgyzstan
-------------------
Information received on 18 Mar 2016 from Dr Ashirbai Zhusupov, deputy director chief state veterinary inspector, State Inspection on Veterinary and Phytosanitary Security, Ministry of Agriculture and Food, Bishkek, Kyrgyzstan

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 13 Mar 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 14 Mar 2016
Report date: 17 Mar 2016
Date event resolved: 14 Mar 2016
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 20 Feb 2015
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Tash-Koro, Alay, Osh
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Mar 2016
Outbreak status: Resolved (14 Mar 2016)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: cattle with cardiac arrhythmia, respiratory arrest, and haemorrhage.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 4 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 25 / 5 / 100 / 25
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country
Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Osh / Cattle / 286 / Live vaccine
Disinfection/disinfestation; quarantine; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The affected village in Osh region is at the westernmost limit of the Uzbek Ferghana valley and reflects the enzootic status in the valley and its overflow into bordering Kyrgyz villages. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4108813,613.]
